post_text:
Update from Superintendent Calkins:

Dear Pocantico Families,

I wanted to provide you with the latest guidance from the New York State Education Department in regard to the mandated NYS 3-8 Assessments. All Elementary and Intermediate State Assessments have been suspended for the remainder of the school year. The suspension applies to the following assessments:

• Grades 3-8 English Language Arts Test;
• Grades 3-8 Mathematics Test;
• Grade 4 Elementary-Level Science Test;
• Grade 8 Intermediate-Level Science Test;
• The English as a Second Language Achievement Test (NYSESLAT) in Grades K-12; and
• NY State Alternate Assessment (NYSAA) for students with severe cognitive disabilities in Grades 3-8 and high school.

We do not have information yet regarding the Regents tests.

My best regards and wash those hands!

Rich

